{"cursor":"22095","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n'Assistive Technology' is an umbrella term that includes assistive, adaptive,\nand rehabilitative devices for people with disabilities and also includes the\nprocess used in selecting, locating, and using them. AT promotes greater\nindependence by enabling people to perform tasks that they were formerly unable\nto accomplish, or had great difficulty accomplishing, by providing enhancements\nto, or changing methods of interacting with, the technology needed to accomplish\nsuch tasks.\n","linknr":628,"url":"Assistive_technology","recorded":1362575088,"links":47,"instances":["in_ict","medicine"],"pdf":["http://glencoe.mcgraw-hill.com/sites/dl/free/0078901359/594902/AAT_v4.pdf","http://glencoe.mcgraw-hill.com/sites/dl/free/0078901359/594902/AAT_v4.pdf"],"categories":["Assistive technology","Disability","Educational technology","Web accessibility"],"headings":["Assistive Technology and Adaptive Technology","Mobility impairment and wheelchairs","Mobility impairment and walkers","Personal Emergency Response Systems","Accessibility software","Assistive Technology for visual impairment","Augmentative and alternative communication","Assistive Technology for Cognition","Prosthesis","Assistive Technology and sports","Computer accessibility","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Handicapped_Accessible_sign.svg/16px-Handicapped_Accessible_sign.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/48/Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg/16px-Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/48/Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg/16px-Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Hoergeraet_analog_050609.jpg/250px-Hoergeraet_analog_050609.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Pride_Jazzy_Select_power_chair_001.JPG/220px-